title: Jesús Martínez
text:
Mathematical scientist with professional experience in the Oil & Gas industry. My contributions range from numerical methods to a variety of statistical analysis.

I’m an individual who enjoys making a difference at the technical level but also as a group member. I believe that developing valuable tools and insights is an iterative and collaborative process.
I’m also interested in computational methods to analyze Multiplexed Immunofluorescence image data. Specifically, I’m interested in spatial methods to draw insights from point-process patterns.

title: Welcome To My Blog
text: I’m still searching deep inside for the motivation to document things I find interesting and publish them. I’ve found it hard to stay motivated when using other media but Quarto has really impressed me. I began using it at work and it is surprisingly easy to use.

title: Notes on Data Structures
text: I was a little bit bored and while looking looking around youtube I came across a 2020 MIT series on Introduction to Algorithms. The first lecture is pretty basic but the second one features one of my favorite MIT online course intructors: Erik Demaine. So I decided to just type his second lecture on Data Structures using Quarto for practice.

title: Notes on Data Structures
text:
API vs Data Structures
First thing is to distinguish between an Application Program Interface (API) and a Data Structure






API: Tells you what you want to do.









Data Structure : Tells you how you do it.
